<div id="feature_1">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/people-of-nasa/goddard-people/jennifer-krottinger-designing-ways-to-serve/">Jennifer Krottinger: Designing Ways to Serve</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/people-of-nasa/goddard-people/jennifer-krottinger-designing-ways-to-serve/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202403_news_krottinger_1472x960.jpg" alt="Photo of Jennifer Krottinger" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/people-of-nasa/goddard-people/jennifer-krottinger-designing-ways-to-serve/">At NASA’s Goddard Institute for Space Studies in New York City, Jennifer Krottinger pairs her artistic vision with a passion for public service.</a>
<span class="feature_date">(2024-03-05)</span></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_1 -->
<div id="feature_2">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/can-volcanic-super-eruptions-lead-to-major-cooling-study-suggests-no/">Can Volcanic Super Eruptions Lead to Major Cooling? Study Suggests No</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/can-volcanic-super-eruptions-lead-to-major-cooling-study-suggests-no/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202403_news_volcanos_1472x960.jpg" alt="Satellite photo of Mount Etna erupting in 2002" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/can-volcanic-super-eruptions-lead-to-major-cooling-study-suggests-no/">New research suggests that sunlight-blocking particles from an extreme eruption would not cool surface temperatures on Earth as severely as previously estimated.</a>
<span class="feature_date">(2024-03-01)</span></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_2 -->
<div id="feature_3">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-launches-new-climate-mission-to-study-ocean-atmosphere/">NASA Launches New Climate Mission to Study Ocean, Atmosphere</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-launches-new-climate-mission-to-study-ocean-atmosphere/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202402_news_pacelaunch_1462x960.jpg" alt="Photo of the rocket carrying PACE lifting off the launch pad" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-launches-new-climate-mission-to-study-ocean-atmosphere/">NASA’s PACE satellite mission to study ocean health, air quality, and the effects of a changing climate for the benefit of humanity launched successfully into orbit at 1:33 a.m. EST, Thursday, February 8.</a>
<span class="feature_date">(2024-02-08)</span></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_3 -->
<div id="feature_4">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-analysis-confirms-2023-as-warmest-year-on-record/">NASA Analysis Confirms 2023 as Warmest Year on Record</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-analysis-confirms-2023-as-warmest-year-on-record/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202401_news_gistemp_1472x960.jpg" alt="Line plot of global temperature anomalies showing the curve for months of 2023 overlying curves of previous years" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-analysis-confirms-2023-as-warmest-year-on-record/">
Earth's average surface temperature in 2023 was the warmest on record, according to an analysis by NASA. Global temperatures last year were around 1.2&#176;C above the 1851-1980 baseline.</a>
<span class="feature_date">(2024-01-12)</span></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_4 -->
<div id="feature_5">
<h2><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/152313/five-factors-to-explain-the-record-heat-in-2023">Five Factors to Explain the Record Heat in 2023</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/152313/five-factors-to-explain-the-record-heat-in-2023"><img src="/gfx/spot/2024/202401_feature_gistempeo_1472x960.jpg" alt="Screen capture from an animation showing the rise of CO2 in Earth;s atmosphere over the past century and how the gas circulates around the globe" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p><a href="https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/152313/five-factors-to-explain-the-record-heat-in-2023">NASA announced that 2023 was the hottest year on record. What caused the year to be so hot? Here is a breakdown of the primary factors that scientists considered.</a>
<span class="feature_date">(2024-01-13)</span></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_5 -->
<div id="feature_6">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/new-nasa-satellite-to-unravel-mysteries-about-clouds-aerosols/">New NASA Satellite To Unravel Mysteries About Clouds, Aerosols</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/new-nasa-satellite-to-unravel-mysteries-about-clouds-aerosols/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202312_news_pace12_1472x960.jpg" alt="Colorful satellite image of clouds over the ocean." /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/new-nasa-satellite-to-unravel-mysteries-about-clouds-aerosols/">NASA’s upcoming PACE mission will offer important insights on airborne particles of sea salt, smoke, human-made pollutants, and dust by observing how they interact with light.</a>
<span class="feature_date">(2023-12-12)</span></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_6 -->
</div><!-- end fbox -->
